sub_title: French Teacher at Stedelijk Gymnasium Leiden and Alliance Francaise Bois-le-Duc
summary:
Professional translator and French teacher (cum laude first degree, ILO - University of Amsterdam, 18 october 2012).
 
Masters degree in French with Italian, Educational Studies and Language acquisition as minors.

I have lived and worked in Paris (France) for five years before deciding to start in another field of studies: Childrens' Development and Educational Studies at the University of Amsterdam (The Netherlands). After finishing my first year, I decided to return working with my passion and entered the post-master program at the ILO to obtain my first degree in teaching French.

During the 5 month transistion period between France and The Netherlands I left for Africa to attend a humanitary program. There I worked in an orphanage, in a micro-financing project (Ghana) and on a multi-discipline work site where school drop-outs were educated for free (Republic of Bénin).

At the moment I am working as a highschool teacher in French and as a French teacher for adults for the Alliance Française. I am also regurlarly involved in translation missions.

My goal is to combine my three passions -languages, childrens development & education and humanitary work.

On november 2nd 2012 I received the Gerard Westhoff Taaldidactiekprijs for my thesis on how to improve spoken French among highschool students. This document has been published on the website of the Expertisecentrum MVT (modern foreign languages): http://www.iclon.leidenuniv.nl/expertisecentrum-mvt/actueel/winnaars-scriptieprijs-2012.html
